<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. S. Hooper, Kew Bull. 26 (3): 577" authorityYear="1972" baseAuthorityName="C. B. Clarke ex Kuek" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Cyperus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyperus tonkinensis var. baikiei" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="tonkinensis" variety="baikiei">Cyperus tonkinensis var. baikiei</taxonomicName>
is not listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org nor assessed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
. The taxon is currently known from five localities. The extent of occurrence of this species is about 800 km2 and the area of occupancy is about 20 km2. Construction of a hydropower dam on the Sanaga River from which the species was collected is in progress. Based on this threat and the fact that the species is only currently known from five localities, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Oxalidaceae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="C. tonkinensis var. baikiei" order="Oxalidales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="variety" species="tonkinensis" variety="baikiei">C. tonkinensis var. baikiei</taxonomicName>
is here assessed as Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Endangered ENB1+2ab (ii, iii)</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
